Ur a inspiration for me (a young girl coming to Indian from Bahrain and living a dream life in the city of dreams 🙌🏼🙌🏼🙏🙏👏🏼👏🏼🧿
thank u for inspiring millions including me !!! I am wishing u more happiness and I know u r a workaholic and perfectionist so  U will live  ur dream for next 100years 🧿❤️🌈

Ps:Thank u for making me social media famous(still remember the day u told me that social media will change the world and ppl thinking and to learn about it and today it just changed  the every one 🙌🏼) and  most importantly helping me to live my life without fear , shame & thought me to take deep breath and move on without any regrets 🙏🌈Happy happy day Jacksy (come back soon😘 ) 🧿❤️🌈🌈🤗…

Thank u @radhikamerchant for trusting me with ur #arangetram & the photo shoot for ur #arangetramBook and most importantly thank u for inspiring & bringing back my  favourite art form  alive in me back 🙌🏼🌈❤️… One of my best experience of my life 🧿. U where amazing and I saw how hard u worked 🙌🏼…. U brought value to one of the most valuable art form we hve in #india 🙌🏼🌈❤️ 

So to all my shines , I hve been a classical trained Bhartanatyam dancer from a very young age in #Germany ! I was blessed to learn by #Savitri mam and it was one of my fav escapes from reality. I used to wait for every Monday to come so that I was able to go and learn and I still remember I even used  to go for my sisters class on Tuesday(she was in a seniors class) and I felt the best being in the class room and see every one dance #bhartanatyam … 

I started to dance from the age of 3  till the age of 14/15 and I had to stop it for some reason which I still feel was the saddest part of my life in childhood. I cried for day and months and I pushed myself to forget the art I loved the most. And today when I got the chance to get Radhika ready for her big day I saw and got inspired to restart again my fav dance form. Thank u #PhawanaMam for helping me with restarting my fav art form 🌈🙏 
 After the Arangetram I was not able to meet anybody else than my ammakutty and we where talking for days about the olden days and I was lucky I was able to bring my @ammakutty17 to the event where I got Radhika ready. A day I will never forget in my life and to all my shines if u love a art don’t listen to anybody. Do what makes u happy because our society has so many opinion and I let go my fav art form because of it. Please all of u do what makes u happy because life is short and do what ur heart loves. #SkyIsNotEvenTheLimit for all of us 🙏 

 A big shout out to the amazing team of Radhika because this day my art would hve never completed so well without all of the team members help and support 🙌🏼🌈❤️

All my #shine’s I am back as a new person. The old Shaan is no more here. It will be the new me who loves the share the real me. … I was living and lie to get the acceptance of the society and I am done doing it!!! … this pandemic I learned to love my choices and I am tired of being a ppl pleaser… I can’t wait to share so many new content which touched me after pandemic and now all my confusion what to do rest of  my life is over !!! I hope my shine know what u want to do rest of ur life. Because life is soooo short and I lost my 20’s for not living my life. I am grateful to every one who helped me to find myself and thank u all to accept me before and I can’t wait to start my new journey with u all. 
#SkyIsNotEvenTheLimit for all of us 🌈❤️

From tomorrow I will be posting all my experience and new series of tutorial’s  and also the best moments of my life with my shines 🙌🏼🙏

11 years before I meet a 20 year old young girl full of dreams and a big responsibility on her shoulders!!!

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
What is real success according society and what is success to u and me and what is the reality of success??? Watch till end and what’s ur opinion ? 

After watching this video what I feel is “just do what makes u happy and do it for urself and live  ur life “!!!

Ps: remember life is very short and do only what makes u happy😉

I was seeing all ur comments saying u guys r missing my #vlogs and I was going through all my footage and I thought I am going to post as many #vlogs I can in between of my movie shedule. 

This was my bride @veeranganaahuja and I am so grateful for this experience because I remember last year in between of my movie  shedule she booked me and finally I made it on time to get her ready on her big day and it changed me a lot ❤️ 

Since last year I was thinking about changing my life and I think it took me time to make the changes in my life and I am ready now for the changes. 
I was sucked in the bussy life the industry gave me and for last 11 years I was so much in my comfort zone doing the same think and I did not even realise how fast life has changed. 

I still remember when I started my career in 2006 and when I was blessed to work with @gopikapillai Mam & @renukapillai_official Mam In Delhi bridal industry and when I moved to Mumbai something I let go without releasing how much fun I had getting every girl ready on her big day  but since last year it was in my mind and I am ready for the change in my life since #pandemic2020😷

Now it’s not only about doing thinks what makes me happy and not the society …I hve  come to a point that I want to do thinks I haven’t done from taking a dance class to going for yoga classes or may be just taking a walk with my little hulk. 

The fear I had what will happen if I take a break from film or #bollywood was stoping me doing a lot of thinks but today I am happy that I hve u all and may be this page might be not any more so interesting for the Bollywood lovers but one think I will promise to all the #makeup #hair lovers … I am here to share my knowledge with u all in small ways and Let the #beautycommunity grow ❤️ 

Ps: in every videos their will be a small trick I share with u all … 
Always make sure ur bride is happy & confident  on her big day. You can always explain ur bride/client what will be the best for her for the day with ur experience … explain and make them understand & always make sure to give the right opinion to  ur client on her big day 

If u hve a happy bride then #SkyIsNotEvenTheLimit for u ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
In 2014 when I started my digital journey I never thought I will live my dream ...I never thought that I will dance again on stage (left Bharatnatyam at the age of 14age) and I never imagined I will
Perform in front of 8000 ppl and that with @jacquelinef143  because for last 10 years what used to give me pure happiness was getting any actress ready for stage performance and I was the luckiest MUA 
 who created crazy looks for jacksy for stage ..when I saw #youtubefanfest I was like wow and I started dreaming and working harder to be part as a #contentcreator to be part of a show for purely content creators and where real love is there...not like Bollywood award function where everything is about the No & Power. 
When I got the call from @sudeeplahiri12 and @gurpreetbhasin to part of @socialnationnow I was speechless and I felt like wow all the sleepless lonely nights and Hustling days was worth it. When some of the top actresses told they don’t want to work with me because of my dream to vlog and I got banned from top actresses I was more and more confused if I should go with the society rule how a celebrity makeup artiest should be. For last 6years I used to be angry/sad and confused if I was right. Because I did not knew if I was right path &the confusion in my head was growing day by day...till last year when #socialnationnow  happend to me ... at this pandemic I am the happiest and luckiest to look back that I am truly blessed to work with ppl like jacksy who supported me from day 1 of my dream of digital vlogging  to come and support me on my big day which nobody I know would had done for free in her status’s 🙌🏻 (Sorry to her managers who was angry at that because nobody  made money for this event 😭😉 and jacksy actually supported my dream ) & guys for longest I was dreaming to dance with her on stage (I am for Eva thankful to u Jacksy for this day ) 
Never let society rules take over ur dream ... be the script writer of ur own life. Make sure u make ur Mom happy by proving u can ... hve a amazing team (my team♥️) who supports and want to grow with u.Make sure u living ur life
 #SkyIsNotEvenTheLimit for all of us 🙌🏻 
#mua to #influencer ♥️
 #Grateful
